### Steps for installation/upgrade CRUX:
1. Boot from CDROM or USB with this image
2. Check & set (if necessary) the correct time on the host:
  date [MMDDhhmm[[CC]YY]
3. Create & format (if necessary) the partition(s) which you want use:
  cfdisk /dev/sda
  mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda1
  mkswap /dev/sda2
4. Mount the partition on which you want to install this distribution:
  mount /dev/sda1 /mnt
5. Activate your swap partition:
  swapon /dev/sda2
6. Run the script to install/upgrade base packages and kernel:
  pkguse -s -r /mnt -u /media/crux BASE
7. "chroot" into your CRUX installation:
  setup-chroot
### Install:
1. Edit /etc/fstab, example:
  /dev/sda1   /         ext4     defaults                         0  1
  /dev/sda2   swap      swap     defaults                         0  0
  /dev/cdrom  /cdrom    iso9660  ro,user,noauto,unhide            0  0
  devpts      /dev/pts  devpts   noexec,nosuid,gid=tty,mode=0620  0  0
  tmp         /tmp      tmpfs    defaults                         0  0
  shm         /dev/shm  tmpfs    defaults                         0  0
2. Edit /etc/lilo.conf, example:
  lba32
  install=text
  boot=/dev/sda
  image=/boot/vmlinuz
    label=CRUX
    initrd=/boot/initrd
    root=/dev/sda1
    append=quiet
    read-only
3. Install boot loader by lilo
4. Edit /etc/rc.conf
5. Set the root password and create admin account, example:
  useradd -G root -s /bin/bash -m -c Administrator admin
  passwd admin
### Upgrade:
1. Update boot loader by lilo
2. Check out the rejects by rejmerge
### Finish:
1. Reboot into the installed/upgraded system
